2026-04-21 02:33:17 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Battery (Power Source)'] hypothesis_explanation="The main clues are: 1) The lamp does not turn on, 2) The green LED on the power supply is off, 3) The red LED on the control module is on, and 4) The battery shows -12.0V internal voltage. The negative (reversed) voltage on the battery indicates it is installed with reversed polarity. The power supply indicator LED is oriented to only light when the polarity is correct (hence it's off), and the red LED in the control module is specifically designed to illuminate when polarity is inverted. Thus, the root cause is reversed polarity at the power source (battery). Reinstalling the battery with the correct polarity should solve the problem."
